<br>
Later that day I wrote myself a letter to read years and years from now, to my kids possibly reflecting how it felt when that happened.<br>
<br>
I didnt really get emotional about it until i saw a video clip on the news that showed a person falling from the WTC, when i saw that, i went into my room and cried for a bit, we had an assembly today and (even though horrbily put together and presented) brought back some memories.<br>
<br>
If the war is still goiing on when i am old enough to enlist, i will sure as hell go spelunking in afghanistan and punch him once for each person who lost their lives, twice for the firefighters, and then a few thousand more times for the hell of it. <p><hr width="267" align="left"><table  width="*" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1"><tr><td  align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168211" target="new"><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/baadansig1a.jpg"></a></td><td  align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="new"><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/azumaan1a.jpg"></a></td></tr><tr><td  align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112720" target="new">51 Half Elf Warrior</a></td><td  align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145036" target="new">34 Erudite Necro</a></td></tr><tr><td  align="center"> &gt;Dragon Maw&lt; </td><td  align="center"> &gt;Dragon Maw&lt;
