<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   I've been awhile on responding to e-mails like this as I have no words to accurately describe what I am feeling. <br>
<br>
Shock, dismay, anger, hatred, sorrow, none of them fit the bill, nothing conveys the numbness that rests in my gut. <br>
<br>
I don't even know who I want to hit back at, the anonymous fucks. But there exists in me the overwhelming urge to hit back, much harder and more viciously than I<br>
was hit...and that scares me. <br>
<br>
In our mad rush to avenge ourselves, we will become our enemies. <br>
<br>
&quot;I beheld what I became, and abhorred what I'd become&quot; - me, after playing thru Wing Commander 4 and playing the evil Blair route. <br>
<br>
I watched &quot;Band of Brothers&quot; last night on HBO and something was conveyed to me, that only this or perhaps the &quot;Saving Private Ryan&quot; could. The utter<br>
dependence that mankind has on violence to solve it's problems. The ultimate threat of any society has is death, that threat was carried out on us by a band of zealots<br>
this last Tuesday. <br>
<br>
My one constant feeling on this is that we must make sure it never happens again and sadly, tragically there is only one way to do this. That is to make the cost so<br>
unbearably, inhumanly, mind numbingly, horrifically high that the cost so far outweighs the gain that it never is even considered as a solution ever again. <br>
<br>
As much as we would like to believe that power does not flow from the barrel of the gun, we must acknowledge and even embrace that fact. <br>
<br>
And yes, I did fire up Rainbow Six and smoked some Tangos.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I dont mean to come off sounding like a hawk, but the Israelis have a ceremony in which they swear in some of their Army officers where they gather on the plataeu of Masada and take the the oath &quot;Sheneeth Lo Tafo&quot; (this is spelled phonetically and incorrectly) which literally translates &quot;Again not, it shall fall.&quot;. <br>
<br>
The people of the United States need to remember that mantra, and also that if we do not take steps to stop the merchants of terrorism they will return and strike us again.<br>
<br>
Sorry to get on my soapbox but after watching the news alot of stuff was dredged up I thought I had put to bed and this is good catharsis.<br>
