</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaielmankajiraliege.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aielman KajiraLiege</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/13/02 8:46:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1253.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Wut were yoo doin 1 year today (sep 11)</span><hr size=1> I was teaching a class that day. I remember distinctly the series of events. I was in NY about 20 miles north of the city. My student's were working on a lab and I was chatting on AIM with one of the girls in the office of the company I worked for. She said &quot;oh my god...i plane just crashed into one of the towers.&quot;  At that point, noone knew what exactly was going on and I was thinking it was some idiot in a cesna who flew too close and paid the price. <br>
<br>
In any case, my 3 students and I filed outside to the balcony of the 2 story building we were on to see if we could see the smoke. At that time, a jumbo jet roared over our heads at about 1000 feet. It seemed a bit ood. It was too fast and high to be landing at Stewart Air Force base, or the Fishkill NY airport, but too low to be doing anything else. 3 min later that plane crashed into the second tower. By that time we were back inside and getting ready for more instruction, when I looked down to see an IM saying the second tower had been hit. I tried to IM back but lost the service. I tried looking up some news but the web was paralyzed. Most web and telephone connections around the NYC area were severely damaged by the damage to the towers. <br>
<br>
There was no TV or radio in the center we were at. One of my students was a NY State fire investigator. The other was a reserve fireman and had 3 brothers who were NYC cops. The third worked for the Red Cross. So we all piled in our cars and headed to my hotel room to watch the news.<br>
<br>
We stood in utter shock and amazment while watching it live on one of the local news channels. As a reporter was talking a screaming body landed not 10 feet behind him and bounced (coverage like that thankfully was edited outside of the local market). Just then, the first tower started to come down. I couldn't believe it. Chuck, the fire investigator's beeper went of before the first debris hit the ground. The other two students received them one after the other and they all headed out. 5 min after they left I got a call from Chuck telling me he was coming back to get me...they wanted as many network guys as they could get.<br>
<br>
I spent the next 5 days at ground zero and the red cross building. I didn't sleep for more than a few minutes for 9 days. I drove home on Sunday to my frantic wife who insisted I not spend another day there. I lost 2 friends in the towers and one friend I served with in the Pentagon. I spent most of the 11th this year trying not to break into tears every time I saw a picture on the television of a fireman or of the towers, which was so frequent I had to keep the tv off all day.<br>
<br>
I don't care what anyone says. I don't care what anyone thinks. I saw it...I felt it...I smelled it, which is the one thing I will never forget. For what they did I want to scour the earth for every last person who was responsible for this attrocity, no matter what their motivation was, and kill them...slowly and painfully. I want to film it as we bury them with a pig, which according to the moslem faith, will bar them from paradise and consign them to hell, and then distribute that film to every news agency in the world so everyone can see. Screw anyone who gets in the way. We told you we were coming. Move it or lose it...train coming.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
Birds of Prey, Prexus <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/azarielleeq/images/aieldon.jpg">
